# PrimeNG — Use It Everywhere

PrimeNG is the **only** UI component library for this project. Never hand-roll
interactive elements when a PrimeNG equivalent exists.

## Required substitutions

| Raw HTML | PrimeNG replacement |
|----------|---------------------|
| `<button>` | `<p-button>` (import `ButtonModule`) |
| `<input>` | `<p-inputtext>` / `<p-input-group>` |
| Loading skeletons | `<p-skeleton>` (import `SkeletonModule`) |
| Error messages | `<p-message>` (import `MessageModule`) |
| Toasts | `<p-toast>` + `MessageService` (import `ToastModule`) |
| Tooltips | `pTooltip` directive (import `TooltipModule`) — already correct |
| File tree | `<p-tree>` (import `TreeModule`) — already correct |

## Icon-only buttons

Use `pButton` directive with `[rounded]="true"` and `[text]="true"`:

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — raw button -->
<button class="icon-btn" (click)="doThing()">
  <i class="pi pi-folder-open"></i>
</button>

<!-- ✅ GOOD — PrimeNG -->
<p-button
  icon="pi pi-folder-open"
  [text]="true"
  [rounded]="true"
  size="small"
  pTooltip="Open another folder"
  (onClick)="doThing()"
/>
```

## Skeleton loading

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — custom divs -->
<div class="skeleton-row" [style.width]="w"></div>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<p-skeleton height="0.875rem" [style]="{ width: w }" />
```

## Imports

Always add the relevant module to the component's `imports: []` array.
Never add styles for things PrimeNG already handles.
